rComments: I went into this course having known a bit of C programming which I recommend. If you understood the topics & assignments then the exams will be not hard. Labs were a bit tedious. The project was the toughest so I'd find a good partner/get help if you need. Prof is clear in explaining the topics and I think he's a solid EECS prof for any course.
That exam was terrible, I barely finished it
His lectures are actually ok. But final exam was insanely difficult, it didnt not reflect what he covered in class. He purposely made the questions really hard to understand. Stay away from him !
If he could do some hand writing examples instead of just using PPT. It might more helpful for students to understand the concepts quickly.

He's an excellent prof! He's always there to answer your questions, explains everything clearly and his exams are very similar to review questions that he posts during exam weeks. Even though labs and project takes a bit of time to understand and write, his assignments are the main thing to understand the course. During lectures he gives bonus!
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: It's comical how little Prof. Ahmed knows. Linear Systems is his specialization yet he makes mistakes with his teaching. As a prof, I lost all credibility with him. Nice guy though, marks quite generously. The midterm was exactly the assignment questions. Final is yet to be seen.

Mohamed Ahmed is honestly a great prof. Sometime he may go off topic, however he teaches the course content well and teaches what you need to know. He's ALWAYS available to help students. Don't trust these low gpa people that complain because they're just naturally untalented. Study, do your homework, work hard and you'll do very well.

His lectures are useless, it's better to just study them at home by yourself. He gives out assignments on a weekly basis in which some require you to use multisim which means you may have to buy a license or get a 0 on the assignment. The final exam is hard and has a multiple choice section which if you get the answer wrong you get -1 points
Teaching style involves rushed explanation of concepts with very little detail. Questions asked during the class are dodged and never addressed again. Exams don't reflect course content well. Avoid!

Incompetent. 95% of the exam was about the last 5% of the course, which he didnt teach well. The preparation questions he did for the exam were nothing like the exam. Im pretty sure another professor wrote our final exam, but if he wrote it then hes cruel as well as incompetent

This professor is the worst of the worst. He does not teach materials properly and is ALWAYS last minute. He taught us material 2 days before our final exam and when i say taught, he blabbered nonsense that made no sense. He is the WORST. KEEP AWAY FROM THS PROF. He uses Galko's notes. I don't even think he understands in Galko's notes.

His lecture is useless, you can just study at home through his PPTs(btw, the ppts of this course are made by another professor ). This course is hard, but the midterm is easy to get a+ if you understand all the materials in ppt and do all the assignments by yourself. Therefore i suggest that if you want to get a high grade, do more practices.
Rate for 1 star because there is no option of giving 0 or minus stars. Do NOT take his class if you have other options.
